333; Thomas, C.D., Cameron, A., Green, R.E., Bakkenes, M., Beaumont, L.J., Collingham, Y.C., Erasmus, B.F.N., Williams, S.E., Extinction risk from climate change (2004) Nature, 427 (6970), pp. 145-148. , DOI 10.1038/nature02121; Thomas, J.A., Telfer, M.G., Roy, D.B., Preston, C.D., Greenwood, J.J.D., Asher, J., Fox, R., Lawton, J.H., Comparative Losses of British Butterflies, Birds, and Plants and the Global Extinction Crisis (2004) Science, 303 (5665), pp. 1879-1881. , DOI 10.1126/science.1095046; Thuiller, W., Broennimann, O., Hughes, G., Alkemade, J.M., Midgley, G.F., Corsi, F., Vulnerability of African mammals to anthropogenic climate change under conservative land transformation assumptions (2006) Global Change Biology, 12, pp. 424-440; Walther, G.-R., Post, E., Convey, P., Menzel, A., Parmesan, C., Beebee, T.J.C., Fromentin, J.-M., Bairlein, F., Ecological responses to recent climate change (2002) Nature, 416 (6879), pp. 389-395. , DOI 10.1038/416389a; Warren, M.S., Hill, J.K., Thomas, J.A., Asher, J., Fox, R., Huntley, B., Roy, D.B., Thomas, C.D., Rapid responses of British butterflies to opposing forces of climate and habitat change (2001) Nature, 414 (6859), pp. 65-69. , DOI 10.1038/35102054; Williams, J.W., Jackson, S.T., Kutzbach, J.E., Projected distribution of novel and disappearing climates by 2100AD (2007) Proceedings of the National Academy of Science, 104, pp. 5738-5742","Willis, S. G.; Institute of Ecosystem Science, School of Biological and Biomedical Sciences, University of Durham, Durham DH1 3LE, United Kingdom; email: s.g.willis@dur.ac.uk",,,,,,,,0364152X,,EMNGD,18491184,"English","Environ. Manage.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-67349120015
